cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper deals with multi-object tracking in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a convex relaxation solution, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of machine learning, cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with optimization techniques, which may place it in the sub-category of artificial intelligence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The problem of multi-object tracking can also be seen as a robotics problem, which may place it in the sub-category of robotics, cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on real-world video sequences, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of multimedia, cs.MM (Multimedia).
